text: Urangeline East is a rural community in the central part of the Riverina. It is situated by road, about 9 kilometres southeast from Urangeline and 19 kilometres east from Bidgeemia. Bendabo Post Office opened on 1 November 1928, was renamed Urangeline East in 1930 and closed in 1971. It was serviced by the Rand branch railway line before the line was closed in 1975. ==Notes and references== ==External links== * Urangeline East Railway Siding Category:Towns in the Riverina Category:Towns in New South Wales
